  "biography_html": "<div class=\"research-section\">\n<p class=\"research-text\">Sosthenes of Cnidus was a Greek historian known only from a single citation by the Roman author Aulus Gellius. He was active in the 4th century BCE, as his work concerned Philip II of Macedon.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">His sole attested work is the lost History of Philip, referenced in Aulus Gellius&#x27; Attic Nights. No fragments or descriptions of its content are extant.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">Sosthenes is a minor figure, significant only as one of several lost historians who documented the rise of Macedon under Philip II. His work would have offered a contemporary perspective, but its complete loss prevents any assessment of its historical value or style.</p>\n</div>",
